		<td colspan="2">
			
			


<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black"><p><b>Compatible classes:</b></font><br>


<font face="verdana" size="1" color="black">
<a href='classes.asp?CID=3&mode=details&type=races'>Enchanter</a>, <a href='classes.asp?CID=9&mode=details&type=races'>Cleric</a>, <a href='classes.asp?CID=10&mode=details&type=races'>Magician</a>, <a href='classes.asp?CID=12&mode=details&type=races'>Necromancer</a>, <a href='classes.asp?CID=13&mode=details&type=races'>Paladin</a>, <a href='classes.asp?CID=19&mode=details&type=races'>Wizard</a>
<font face="verdana" size="3" color="black"><p><b>Guide:</b></font><br><br>
<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
The final variant of the Human race. Being the exact opposite of the Barbarians, the High Man prides himself on his intellectual abilities and social graces, to the almost total exclusion of the physical disciplines.
			
			</p></font>
