	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#D6D1BE">	
		
	
			</font>
			<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>
			<font color="black">--Submited by:&nbsp;
			<a href="mailto:aburner@rcn.com">Desdinova</a></font> 
			<font color="black">On:&nbsp;05/18/1999 2:01:35 PM</font></b></font>
	
		</td>
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Playing an Erudite is an interesting, often<BR>
frustrating choice.  But for some people, the<BR>
lure of a base 107 INT (117 if you choose a <BR>
spellslinging class) is too much to resist.  Plus<BR>
we look darned spiffy in our Middle Eastern-type<BR>
garb.  (Fully armored Erudite Paladins look way<BR>
cool.)<BR>
<BR>
So here are some hints and tips I've learned<BR>
playing several Erudite characters, the highest<BR>
of which is my 9th level Magician.<BR>
<BR>
1. The guards in the Toxxulia Forest won't help<BR>
you if you're being attacked by Rungupp or the<BR>
Poachers (or any other named NPC, for that matter).<BR>
If one of these guys is whaling on you, zip down<BR>
the tunnel to Erudin and zone to safety.<BR>
<BR>
2.  Practice running around the Toxx at night<BR>
without any light sources.  Believe me when I tell<BR>
you that if you can develop the ability to find your<BR>
way around the Toxx at night, you'll be *miles*<BR>
ahead of the game when you get to places like the<BR>
Karana Plains.<BR>
<BR>
3.  Don't tackle Kerra Isle until you're at least<BR>
6th level, and don't think of doing it solo until<BR>
you're about 12th level.<BR>
<BR>
4.  When you hit 6th-7th level, you will begin to<BR>
find that things in the Toxx won't give you any<BR>
XP.  At that point it's time to move on, and you<BR>
have a choice to make:  Stay bound in Erudin, or<BR>
get bound to someplace else.  Many folks would<BR>
suggest getting bound to a different city, but my<BR>
suggestion is to stay bound to Erudin.  Sure, it's<BR>
a pain if you die, but I personally think that<BR>
it's much nicer to be able to gate back to Erudin<BR>
when you're encumbered with loot (something that<BR>
could happen in short order if you didn't dump any<BR>
points into strength).  This is useful because<BR>
unless you've been working on your factions, you'll<BR>
get shafted on prices by most merchants and some<BR>
won't even sell to you.<BR>
<BR>
5. On a related note, the best bang for the buck<BR>
I've found for 7th level is the Western Karana<BR>
plains.  But drop a couple points into tailoring<BR>
and buy yourself a sewing kit so you can take all<BR>
those pelts you get and turn 'em into something<BR>
that will make you some cash.<BR>
<BR>
6.  Many people will tell you that the quests you<BR>
get at the Temple of Quellios are for Clerics and<BR>
Paladins only.  As near as I can tell, this isn't<BR>
true.  If you're a follower of Quellios, you can<BR>
undertake the Quellios quests (Kobold Shaman's Paw,<BR>
Box of Bones, Staff of the Peacekeepers) yourself,<BR>
and you can do them repeatedly.  I must have<BR>
completed the Kobold Shaman's Paw quest a couple<BR>
dozen times.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck, Cousin Erudite.  May Quellios smile<BR>
upon you!<BR>
<BR>
Desdinova<BR>
Humble Erudite Conjurer of the 3rd Circle<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
