			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A couple of things I've learned advancing to 20th level as an Erudite wizard<BR>
<BR>
1. Hunting in Tox is a hard way to go.<BR>
I shelved the character for a couple of months because of frustration with dying and not<BR>
being able to find the body (/loc is now on a hot key).<BR>
I moved to Rivervale and andvanced quickly.<BR>
<BR>
2. Wizards get Heat Sight at 16th level which gives them infravision. A tremendous help.<BR>
<BR>
3. I have good faction with Neriak. I didn't kill any halflings, so I think Erudites must<BR>
start with it. I'd be interested in knowing if other Erudites have good faction.<BR>
<BR>
4. Lavastorm is the best hunting ground for spellcasters from 14th to 20th level. I covered<BR>
that in about two weeks of casual hunting. <BR>
Lavastorm is right next to Neriak which means I can hit the bank and buy muffins and milk<BR>
while other non-evils have to run invis through Nektulos woods to get to Freeport. <BR>
<BR>
5. Soloing with an Erudite wizard is still easy at 20th level. I gave up on my warrior<BR>
at sixteenth because it became fruitless to solo. 30 minutes to recover health? Come on!<BR>
I recover my mana in less than 5 minutes, and can easily take anything that con's blue to <BR>
me.<BR>

